===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|grove}}, {{m|enm|grave}}, from {{inh|en|ang|grāf}}, {{m|ang|grāfa|t=grove; [[copse]]}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*graib}}, {{m|gmw-pro|*graibō|t=branch, group of branches, thicket}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*graibaz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*graibô|t=branch, fork}}, which could be related to {{m|gem-pro|*grabaną|t=to dig}}.<ref>Puppel, S. (2010). Language History and Linguistic Modelling: A Festschrift for Jacek Fisiak on His 60th Birthday. Germany: De Gruyter., p. 134-135</ref>

Related to {{cog|ang|grǣf}}, {{m|ang|grǣfe|t=brushwood; thicket; copse}}, {{cog|ang|grǣfa|t=thicket}}, dialectal {{cog|no|greive|t=ram with splayed horns}}, dialectal {{cog|no|greivlar|t=ramifications of an antler}}, dialectal {{cog|no|grivla|t=to branch, branch out}}, {{cog|non|grein|t=twig, branch, limb}}. More at {{l|en|greave}}.

